<br>
Rangers are getting summoned and ping ponging all over the place, that is to be expected. However, I did notice something very nice today with regards to warriors (and perhaps other tank classes as well).... TAUNT<br>
<br>
This will require some more testing, but our plain ol taunt key seems to have received a stealth boost in the april 8 aggro changes. Some background and examples....<br>
<br>
No one has been certain about how the inner workings of Taunt figure out whether you succeed or fail when you hit the button. It's obviously more complicated than just a skill check, because there are certain trends you can see (such as if a shaman slows a mob on the pull before you have a couple seconds of melee, it ALWAYS took me at least 2 taunts to get aggro back, never succeeded on the first try)<br>
<br>
As of tonight, those trends have changed. I have been able to snag aggro off an early slow first try, and in an exp group with 2 warriors earlier, the other tank was able to grab aggro off mobs I had been off-tanking for like 20 percent of their health.... with a single normal taunt. Pretty consistently. Up until now, I've only been able to make that happen with AE taunt.<br>
<br>
I've been of the opinion for a while that part of taunt's logic was an upper limit on how far it could move you up the hate list with a single use (based on my impressions through hundreds of hours of grinding). It would seem that as of tonight, those restrictions have been relaxed, or removed.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, don't take any of my guesses at the inner workings of taunt as fact, but I'm positive that in some ways, taunt was working better tonight for me than ever before.<br>
<br>
