<br>
About taunt itself, I will say nothing... Because we have no way to know exactly how it works. IMO it works about 60 to 75% of times, with some modifiers for :<br>
- How you consider the target.<br>
- How far you are from the top of the aggro list.<br>
- If you /shield the player on top of the list it works a lot more.<br>
<br>
However, as long we don't know if taunt is a Fail or Sucess roll, or if there's some &quot;half roll&quot; with it, we cannot parse it efficiency. It would be great to have some &quot;You have taunted %t successfully&quot;  or &quot;You failled to taunt %t&quot; messages...<br>
<br>
I'd like to have a statement from one of the developpers... something like : &quot;Taunt work like this and this, and in So and So situation it works like that, and we are changing this and this&quot;<br>
